 The world-sheet diagram for the one-point function. 
  
The only vertex in the theory is a prescription for gluing three strips
together.  The right half of the first strip is glued to the left half
of the second and similarly for the second and third strips and 
the third and first strips.

Using these rules we can construct the one-point amplitude.  
We start with an external state  which propagates along
a strip of length .
We then  take a second strip of length  and glue both ends of
it and the end of the first propagator together using the vertex.
