This approximation to the function  is obtained by numerically
determining the rate of convergence for several points at fixed values
of  using the ansatz .  Since the first terms
dropped in the level  truncation are of order , we indeed
expect , in close agreement with our empirical data.  These
results are consistent with the general empirical observation that,
while integrated amplitudes converge polynomially in  (when
finite), the integrand itself converges exponentially in  with a
rate that depends on the modular parameter.

