cancel this surface term.  Unfortunately, for the divergent diagrams,
we can not define this region of integration. Thus we consider
replacing the  region of integration with a new diagram.
 We then try to understand what restrictions the condition of
BRST invariance imposes.  This condition will not fix the new
diagram completely but will tell us something about the physics
of the  region.

To construct the new diagram, we start with the surface term we
found from acting on  with  and
